# Naming and Structure Rules

## Folder Structure
- Always use feature-sliced design: `/src/modules/<feature>/`
- Every module must export only via `index.ts` (barrel export)
- Never create files outside the established structure

## File Naming
- Component files: `PascalCase.tsx` (e.g., `RoomCard.tsx`)
- Hook files: `useSomething.ts` (e.g., `useAuth.ts`)
- Utility files: `camelCase.ts` (e.g., `formatDate.ts`)
- Type files: `types.ts` or `index.ts` within module
- Test files: `*.test.ts` or `*.spec.ts`

## Import Paths
- Always use absolute imports with `@/` prefix
- Never use relative imports going up directories (`../`, `../../`)
- Example: `import { useAuth } from '@/modules/auth'` not `import { useAuth } from '../../modules/auth'`

## Module Structure
Each module should have:
- `index.ts` - Barrel export (public API only)
- `types.ts` - TypeScript types/interfaces
- `hooks/` - Custom hooks (if multiple)
- `components/` - React components (if multiple)
- Internal implementation files (not exported)

## Barrel Exports
- Only export public APIs in `index.ts`
- Keep implementation details private
- Example: Export `useAuth` hook, but not internal `validateToken` function
